Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I go to Page 10 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Transient bone marrow edema ("transient osteoporosis" (TBME))' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And a single selection localizer is enabled
And 'Articular effusion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema' automatically checkbox is enabled and checked
And 'Missing subchondral lesion' automatically checkbox is enabled and checked

And 'Stress fracture' radio button is enabled
And 'Metastasis' radio button is enabled
And 'Osteomyelitis' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Stress fracture' radio button
Then 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Metastasis' radio button
Then 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Osteomyelitis' radio button
Then 'Subordinate' checkbox is enabled
